In the Matter of Frederick ATANASIO, Bankrupt; Frederick Atanasio, Appellant. No. 9181. Circuit Court of Appeals, Third Circuit. Argued Oct. 24, 1946. Decided Nov. 1, 1946. Adolf L. Engelke, of Jersey City, N. J., for appellant. George G. Tennant, of Jersey City, N. J., for Samuel W. Silverman, a creditor. Joseph L. Freiman, of Union City, N. J., for appellee.

Before BIGGS, ALBERT LEE STEPHENS, and KALODNER, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

The order complained of will be affirmed. The restraining order of July 2, 1946, will be vacated.
